msgid "The LXDE Configuration HOWTO"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><abstract>
#: en/lxde-howto.xml:19
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"This guide introduces the user to LXDE, explains its components, and leads the\n"
"user through the installation.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><title>
#: en/lxde-howto.xml:32
#, no-wrap
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/lxde-howto.xml:34
#, no-wrap
msgid "What is LXDE?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/lxde-howto.xml:38
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"After installing your base Gentoo system, and <uri\n"
"link=\"https://wiki.gentoo.org/wiki/Xorg/Configuration\">the X Server</uri>, you have to make many\n"
"choices regarding your graphical environment, if you want one at all. There\n"
"are many options available to you, ranging from minimalistic window managers\n"
"like <uri link=\"/doc/en/openbox.xml\">Openbox</uri>, to full-featured\n"
"desktop environments like <uri link=\"http://wiki.gentoo.org/wiki/KDE\">\n"
"KDE</uri>, and <uri link=\"/doc/en/gnome-config.xml\">GNOME</uri>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/lxde-howto.xml:48
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You may find yourself saying \"well, I like the idea of having a lightweight\n"
"graphical environment, but I don't want to install and configure every\n"
"component individually like with Openbox.\" For quite some time, such users\n"
"installed <uri link=\"/doc/en/xfce-config.xml\">Xfce</uri>. While it provides\n"
"a nice full-featured environment without the extensive resource usage of KDE or\n"
"GNOME, it could still become a bit on the heavy side. Now, you have another\n"
"choice: the <uri link=\"http://www.lxde.org\">Lightweight X11 Desktop\n"
"Environment</uri>, or <uri link=\"http://www.lxde.org\">LXDE</uri> for short.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/lxde-howto.xml:61
#, no-wrap
msgid "Components of LXDE"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/lxde-howto.xml:65
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"LXDE, being a desktop environment, is comprised of several components. Each\n"
"program offers a certain functionality, and together they form the complete\n"
"desktop environment. Currently, there are eleven core components, and several\n"
"other programs necessary to make a complete LXDE installation. These programs\n"
"are the ones pulled in by the <uri\n"
"link=\"http://packages.gentoo.org/package/lxde-base/lxde-meta\">LXDE meta</uri>\n"
"package, discussed in the installation section.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/lxde-howto.xml:77
#, no-wrap
msgid "Core Components"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/lxde-howto.xml:82
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    <uri\n"
"    link=\"http://packages.gentoo.org/package/lxde-base/lxappearance\">LXappearance</uri>\n"
"    is a GTK theme and icon configurator that allows you to customise the look\n"
"    of LXDE\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/lxde-howto.xml:88
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    <uri\n"
"    link=\"http://packages.gentoo.org/package/lxde-base/lxde-common\">LXDE-common</uri>\n"
"    is a collection of default configuration files and the main set of icons\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/lxde-howto.xml:93
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    <uri\n"
"    link=\"http://packages.gentoo.org/package/lxde-base/lxmenu-data\">LXmenu-data</uri>\n"
"    is the application menu manager\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/lxde-howto.xml:98
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    <uri\n"
"    link=\"http://packages.gentoo.org/package/lxde-base/lxinput\">LXinput</uri> is\n"
"    a keyboard and mouse configurator\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/lxde-howto.xml:103
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    <uri\n"
"    link=\"http://packages.gentoo.org/package/lxde-base/lxpanel\">LXpanel</uri> is\n"
"    the panel that includes the application menu, system tray, and clock\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/lxde-howto.xml:108
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    <uri\n"
"    link=\"http://packages.gentoo.org/package/lxde-base/lxrandr\">LXrandr</uri> is\n"
"    a graphical interface to X Resize and Rotate, allowing for display\n"
"    manipulation\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/lxde-howto.xml:114
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    <uri\n"
"    link=\"http://packages.gentoo.org/package/lxde-base/lxsession\">LXsession</uri>\n"
"    is a session manager, providing options to shutdown, reboot, and suspend the\n"
"    system\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/lxde-howto.xml:120
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    <uri link=\"http://packages.gentoo.org/package/lxde-base/lxsession-edit\">\n"
"    LXsession-edit</uri> allows you to enable/disable applications at startup\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/lxde-howto.xml:124
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    <uri\n"
"    link=\"http://packages.gentoo.org/package/lxde-base/lxshortcut\">LXshortcut</uri>\n"
"    is an easy way to edit application shortcuts, especially for desktop icons\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/lxde-howto.xml:129
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    <uri link=\"http://packages.gentoo.org/package/lxde-base/lxtask\">LXtask</uri>\n"
"    is the task manager used to view/edit running services and programs\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/lxde-howto.xml:133
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    <uri\n"
"    link=\"http://packages.gentoo.org/package/lxde-base/lxterminal\">LXterminal</uri>\n"
"    is the vte-based tabbed terminal emulator\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/lxde-howto.xml:142
#, no-wrap
msgid "Other Applications used by LXDE"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/lxde-howto.xml:147
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    <uri\n"
"    link=\"http://packages.gentoo.org/package/x11-wm/openbox\">OpenBox</uri>\n"
"    is the window manager, responsible for drawing the containers for programs\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/lxde-howto.xml:152
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    <uri\n"
"    link=\"http://packages.gentoo.org/package/x11-misc/pcmanfm\">PCManFM</uri> is\n"
"    the incredibly fast, tabbed file manager\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/lxde-howto.xml:157
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    <uri\n"
"    link=\"http://packages.gentoo.org/package/x11-misc/obconf\">ObConf</uri> is\n"
"    the configurator for OpenBox, allowing you to change window decorations\n"
"    and more\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/lxde-howto.xml:163
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    <uri link=\"http://packages.gentoo.org/package/media-gfx/gpicview\">GPicView\n"
"    </uri> is the default image viewer\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><title>
#: en/lxde-howto.xml:173
#, no-wrap
msgid "Installation"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/lxde-howto.xml:175
#, no-wrap
msgid "Initial installation"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/lxde-howto.xml:179
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"After you have emerged and configured <uri\n"
"link=\"https://wiki.gentoo.org/wiki/Xorg/Configuration\">xorg-server</uri>, you are ready to install LXDE.\n"
"While you may install each component individually, the more efficient and\n"
"preferred method is to emerge the meta package set:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/lxde-howto.xml:185
#, no-wrap
msgid "Installing LXDE"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/lxde-howto.xml:186
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>emerge -av lxde-meta</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/lxde-howto.xml:190
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If everything looks to your liking (meaning the current set of USE flags, \n"
"etc.), then say \"yes\" when asked if you want to emerge the packages.  \n"
"Just like with other desktop environments, you will need to tell the\n"
"X Server to load LXDE automatically, by adding it to your\n"
"<path>~/.xinitrc</path>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/lxde-howto.xml:197
#, no-wrap
msgid "Adding LXDE to your .xinitrc"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/lxde-howto.xml:198
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ <i>echo \"exec startlxde\" >> ~/.xinitrc</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/lxde-howto.xml:202
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"This will automatically start your LXDE session when you type <c>startx</c>\n"
"at the console.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><note>
#: en/lxde-howto.xml:207
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you use a login manager like SLiM, XDM, GDM, or KDM, you do not need to\n"
"edit your <path>~/.xinitrc</path>. LXDE will simply show up as a choice in\n"
"your login manager's screen.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><impo>
#: en/lxde-howto.xml:213
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"As each user has his or her own <path>.xinitrc</path>, you need to make sure to\n"
"issue that command as <e>your user</e>, not as root.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><title>
#: en/lxde-howto.xml:222
#, no-wrap
msgid "Configuration"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/lxde-howto.xml:224
#, no-wrap
msgid "GTK icon warning"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/lxde-howto.xml:228
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Now that the X server knows to start LXDE on command, type in <c>startx</c> to\n"
"fire up LXDE. The first thing you may notice is that you get a warning about an\n"
"improper GTK icon set. To fix this minor hangup, you simply need to change the\n"
"icon theme. To do so, click on the LXDE application menu (in the lower left-hand\n"
"corner of the panel), and go to Preferences --> Appearance.  In the LXappearance\n"
"menu, click on the \"Icon\" tab, and choose nuoveXT.2.2.  Hit \"Apply,\" and then\n"
"\"Close.\" The next time you login to LXDE, the error message will not appear.\n"
"However, you are not limited to using the nuoveXT.2.2 icon theme. You may\n"
"install any other icon theme through LXappearance, and when it is selected, the\n"
"GTK icon warning will no longer appear when starting PCManFM.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/lxde-howto.xml:243
#, no-wrap
msgid "Right-click menu"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/lxde-howto.xml:247
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"In LXDE, every appearance option is not handled through LXappearance as one\n"
"might believe. Rather, there are some common options that are handled through\n"
"a right-click menu on the desktop. At the bottom of that menu is the\n"
"\"Desktop Settings\" menu. In here, you can find icon sizes, single-click and\n"
"double-click behavior, maximum thumbnail size, and desktop wallpaper\n"
"settings. It may behoove you to look through the these tabs for additional\n"
"appearance settings.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><note>
#: en/lxde-howto.xml:257
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"These \"Desktop Settings\" can also be found by opening up the file manager\n"
"(PCManFM), and going to Edit --> Preferences.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><title>
#: en/lxde-howto.xml:266
#, no-wrap
msgid "Further documentation"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/lxde-howto.xml:268
#, no-wrap
msgid "External resources"
msgstr ""

